Data Visualization Lets see how un employement rate is being affected with year ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} ggplot(cleaned_fed_funds1) + aes(x = `Inflation Rate`, y = `Unemployment Rate`) + geom_point(colour = "#69b3a2") + theme_minimal() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Homework_2_Tejaswini_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-16-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} a <- cleaned_fed_funds1 %>% select(Year, `Real GDP (Percent Change)`, `Inflation Rate`) %>% gather(key = "variable", value = "value", -Year) ggplot(a, aes(x =`Year`, y = value)) + geom_line(aes(color = variable, linetype = variable)) + scale_color_manual(values = c("darkred", "steelblue"))+labs( title = "Inflation and gdp change by Year", y = "Variable Rates", x = "Year") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Homework_2_Tejaswini_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-17-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: The entire data set talks about the economic stability of a country.
